record.title: ASIAN ELEPHANT CONSERVATION REAUTHORIZATION ACT OF 2007
record.narrative:
ASIAN ELEPHANT CONSERVATION REAUTHORIZATION ACT OF 2007 -- (Senate - November 16, 2007)

[Page: S14656]

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the Senate proceed to the immediate consideration of Calendar No. 323, H.R. 465.

record.chair: The clerk will state the bill by title.
The assistant legislative clerk read as follows:
A bill (H.R. 465) to reauthorize the Asian Elephant Conservation Act of 1997.
record.narrative: There being no objection, the Senate proceeded to consider the bill.

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the bill be read the third time, passed, the motion to reconsider be laid upon the table, that any statements relating thereto be printed in the Record, without further intervening action or debate.

record.chair: Without objection, it is so ordered.
The bill (H.R. 465) was ordered to a third reading, was read the third time, and passed.
